---
    import "../styles/global.css";
---

<section class="hero-about">
    <div class="hero-left">
      <div class="eyebrow">
        <div class="eyebrow-dash"></div>
        <span class="eyebrow-text">About me</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="page-title">The person<br>behind the <em>code</em></h1>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-right">
      <div class="avatar-wrap">
        <div class="avatar-ring"><div class="avatar-dot"></div></div>
        <span class="avatar-initials">HT</span>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-bio">
        I'm <strong>Hawana Tamang</strong>, a programmer from <strong>Bhaktapur, Nepal</strong> who builds things for the web. My days are split between crafting Spring Boot backends, building custom WordPress solutions, and learning something new — usually at 2am.
      </p>
      <p class="hero-bio">
        I graduated with a <strong>BIT from KIST College, Purbanchal University</strong> and spent over a year at WPDrops building client projects. Now I'm doubling down on backend engineering — REST APIs, databases, and the messy details in between.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <div class="stat-row">
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat-num">1+</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Years experience</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat-num">10+</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Projects shipped</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat-num">2</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Stacks mastered</div>
    </div>
  </div>
   <section class="sec">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">01</span>
      <span class="sec-title">My story</span>
      <div class="sec-line"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="story-block" style="animation-delay:0.05s">
        <div class="story-label">How I started</div>
        <p class="story-text">
          It started with a <strong>two-way chat app in C++</strong> — just sockets, threads, and a lot of confusion. That project taught me more about how computers actually communicate than any textbook did. From there I picked up Java, built a Whack-A-Mole game, and got genuinely obsessed with how backend systems are structured.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-block" style="animation-delay:0.15s">
        <div class="story-label">Where I am now</div>
        <p class="story-text">
          After shipping WordPress projects for international clients at WPDrops, I built <strong>AniMatch</strong> — a full-stack platform in Spring Boot with PostgreSQL — to prove to myself I could architect something end-to-end. It's deployed and running. That felt good. I'm now focused on going deeper into backend engineering while staying sharp on the WordPress side.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="sec" style="padding-bottom:0;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;">
    <div class="sec-head" style="padding:0 2rem 0;">
      <span class="sec-num">02</span>
      <span class="sec-title">What I value</span>
      <div class="sec-line"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="val-grid">
      <div class="val-card" style="animation-delay:0.05s">
        <div class="val-icon"><i class="ti ti-layers-subtract" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
        <div class="val-name">Clean architecture</div>
        <p class="val-desc">Code that a stranger can read six months later. Separation of concerns, meaningful naming, and no magic.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="val-card" style="animation-delay:0.1s">
        <div class="val-icon"><i class="ti ti-bolt" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
        <div class="val-name">Performance matters</div>
        <p class="val-desc">A slow API or a 4-second page load isn't a detail — it's the product. I optimize before it becomes a problem.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="val-card" style="animation-delay:0.15s">
        <div class="val-icon"><i class="ti ti-pencil" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
        <div class="val-name">Writing to learn</div>
        <p class="val-desc">I blog about what I build. Explaining something is the fastest way to find out if you actually understand it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="val-card" style="animation-delay:0.2s">
        <div class="val-icon"><i class="ti ti-arrow-up-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
        <div class="val-name">Always shipping</div>
        <p class="val-desc">Deployed and imperfect beats perfect and local. I'd rather get real feedback than chase theoretical polish.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
   <section class="sec">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">03</span>
      <span class="sec-title">Timeline</span>
      <div class="sec-line"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="tl-item" style="animation-delay:0.05s">
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-year">2025</div>
        <div class="tl-role">BIT Graduation — Purbanchal University</div>
        <div class="tl-co">KIST College · Bhaktapur</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item" style="animation-delay:0.12s">
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-year">Jul 2024 – Oct 2025</div>
        <div class="tl-role">Jr WordPress Developer</div>
        <div class="tl-co">WPDrops pvt. ltd</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item" style="animation-delay:0.19s">
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-year">Apr – Jun 2024</div>
        <div class="tl-role">WordPress Developer Internship</div>
        <div class="tl-co">WPDrops pvt. ltd</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item" style="animation-delay:0.26s">
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-year">2024</div>
        <div class="tl-role">Built AniMatch — first full-stack Java project</div>
        <div class="tl-co">Spring Boot · PostgreSQL · Thymeleaf</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item" style="animation-delay:0.33s">
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-year">2022</div>
        <div class="tl-role">Started BIT — wrote first line of C</div>
        <div class="tl-co">KIST College</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">04</span>
      <span class="sec-title">Full stack</span>
      <div class="sec-line"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tech-sec">
      <div class="tech-group" style="animation-delay:0.05s">
        <div class="tech-group-label">Backend</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>Java</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>Spring Boot</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>JPA / Hibernate</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>JWT / OAuth</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>REST APIs</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>PHP / Laravel</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tech-group" style="animation-delay:0.12s">
        <div class="tech-group-label">Databases & tools</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>PostgreSQL</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>SQL</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>Git</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>Postman</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>Python</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>C / C++</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tech-group" style="animation-delay:0.19s">
        <div class="tech-group-label">Frontend & CMS</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>WordPress</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>Gutenberg blocks</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>React.js</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>Thymeleaf</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>HTML / CSS</div>
        <div class="tech-item"><div class="tech-dot"></div>JavaScript</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">05</span>
      <span class="sec-title">Outside of code</span>
      <div class="sec-line"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="outside-grid">
      <div class="outside-card" style="animation-delay:0.05s">
        <div class="outside-icon"><i class="ti ti-writing" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
        <div class="outside-title">Technical writing</div>
        <p class="outside-desc">I write blog posts about backend concepts — APIs, databases, auth patterns — mostly to solidify my own understanding.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="outside-card" style="animation-delay:0.12s">
        <div class="outside-icon"><i class="ti ti-mountain" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
        <div class="outside-title">Exploring Bhaktapur</div>
        <p class="outside-desc">Living in one of Nepal's most historic cities means there's always somewhere new to walk when a debugging session needs a break.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="outside-card" style="animation-delay:0.19s">
        <div class="outside-icon"><i class="ti ti-device-gamepad-2" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
        <div class="outside-title">Building for fun</div>
        <p class="outside-desc">Side projects with no clients and no deadlines. That's where the Whack-A-Mole game and AniMatch came from.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <div class="cta-band">
    <div class="cta-text">
      <h2>Want to work together?</h2>
      <p>I'm open to backend roles, WordPress projects, and freelance work.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cta-btns">
      <button class="btn-gold">Get in touch</button>
      <button class="btn-outline">View work</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
        const obs = new IntersectionObserver(entries => {
    entries.forEach(e => {
        if(e.isIntersecting) e.target.style.animationPlayState = 'running';
    });
    },{threshold:0.08});

    document.querySelectorAll('.story-block,.val-card,.tl-item,.tech-group,.outside-card,.cta-band').forEach(el => {
    el.style.animationPlayState = 'paused';
    obs.observe(el);
    });
  </script>